Japan
- Mainly Tokyo area. 8 Oct 2014. Dengue (reported) more than 150 cases since August 2014.
http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/kyodo-news-international/141008/japan-draft-dengue-fever-prevention-guidelines

[A public sector health professional has continued to provide information about the dengue outbreak in Japan. Because the reports cited here provide a good, current summary, those other reports are not included, but the individual who provided them is thanked.

Maps of Japan can be accessed at http://mapsof.net/uploads/static-maps/cities_of_japan_map.png and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2856793,156. - Mod.TY]

- Shizuoka prefecture. 29 Sep 2014. Dengue. The Japanese government said [Mon 29 Sep 2014] that a man in Shizuoka Prefecture was infected with a new-type dengue fever virus as it has a different genetic sequence from that of the virus detected in other people in Japan since August [2014]. The man developed dengue symptoms on 10 Sep [2014] and was identified on 18 Sep [2014]. The site of his infection has not been fixed as he said he visited Tokyo in early September and was bitten by a mosquito 9 or 10 Sep [2014] in the eastern part of Shizuoka.
http://www.shanghaidaily.com/article/article_xinhua.aspx?id=243890

[Details that led to the determination that the dengue virus is a new type are not provided. It seems unlikely that the virus is something other than dengue viruses 1-4. Perhaps it is a subtype, or a virus other than the dengue virus type 1 that is causing the cases in the Tokyo area.

